{"id":"friction-8","label":"Friction","lockAfter":2,"list":[{"id":"mcq","label":"Choose the correct answer","type":"mcq","commonData":{"title":"Multiple Choice Questions"},"data":[{"questions":[{"qText":"Friction is ____.","options":"a contact force, a non-contact force, an electrostatic force, a magnetic force"},{"qText":"Which of the following produces least friction?","options":"Rolling friction, Sliding friction, Static friction, Dynamic friction"},{"qText":"Friction always ____.","options":"* opposes the motion\n            helps the motion\n            both (a) and (b)\n            neither (a) nor (b)"},{"qText":"Friction can be reduced by using ____.","options":"oil\n            grease\n            powder\n            * all of these"},{"qText":"Static friction is less than _____.","options":"sliding friction\n            rolling friction\n            both (a) and (b)\n            * neither (a) nor (b)"}]},{"questions":[{"qText":"Whenever the surfaces in contact tend to move or move with respect to each other, the force of friction comes into play _____.","bigOptions":true,"options":"irrespective of whether the objects are solid, liquid or gaseous\n              only if the objects are solid\n        only if one of the two objects is liquid\n        only if one of the two objects is gaseous"},{"qText":"To sharpen the blade of a knife by rubbing it against a surface, which of the following will be most suitable?","options":"Stone, Plastic block, Wooden block, Glass block"},{"qText":"The shape of an aeroplane is like a ____.","options":"bird, dog, car, fish"},{"qText":"Friction is _____.","options":"both friend and foe, a friend, a foe"},{"qText":"Friction due to fluids is called _____.","options":"drag, force, pressure, friction"}]},{"questions":[{"qText":"Which of the following is not a smooth surface?","options":"Surface of tyres, Surface of wet soap, Glazed tiles, Surface of mirror"},{"qText":"A toy car released with the same initial speed will travel farthest on ____.","options":"polished marble surface, cemented surface, brick surface, muddy surface"},{"qText":"If we apply oil on door hinges, the friction will ____.","options":"decrease, increase, disappear, remain unchanged"},{"qText":"Lubricants ______","options":"reduce friction, increase friction, remove friction."},{"qText":"Force of friction depends on ______.","options":"roughness of surface\n              inclination of surface\n              * both (a) and (b)\n              neither (a) nor (b)"}]},{"questions":[{"qText":"Force of friction depends on","options":"roughness of surface\n              weight\n        size\n        * all of these"},{"qText":"What ar fluids?","options":"liquids\n              gases\n              * both (a) and (b)\n              neither (a) nor (b)"},{"qText":"Which is a streamlined object?","options":"Boats\n              Ships\n              Aeroplanes\n              *All of these"},{"qText":"Smooth surface has ____.","options":"* less friction, more friction, sometimes less and sometimes more"},{"qText":"Which of the following is responsible for wearing out of bicycle tyres?","options":"Frictional force, Muscular force, Magnetic force, Electrostatic force"}]},{"questions":[{"qText":"It is difficult to walk on an oily floor because","options":"force of friction is very less, floor gets spoiled, force of friction is high, there is more resistance"},{"qText":"Spring balance is a device used for measuring the __________ acting on an object.","options":"force, mass, pressure"},{"qText":"A matchstick struck on a matchbox catches fire easily because ___.","options":"friction causes fire, of chemical reaction, fire is stored in match stick"},{"qText":"Tyres are treaded to ____.","options":"increase friction, increase its longivity, look good, increase the weight of the tyre"},{"qText":"Sliding friction is _________ rolling friction","options":"greater than, smaller than, equal to"}]},{"questions":[{"qText":"The frictional force exerted by fluids is also called ______. ","options":"drag, drop, drug, drown"},{"qText":"A boat or an aeroplane has a pointed or tapering front / head. Why?","options":"To reduce the friction of fluid, To increase the friction of fluid, To look good, For no reason"},{"qText":"The sole of the shoes becomes plain after wearing it for several months. The reason is ____.","options":"Wearing out due to friction, Wearing out due to no friction, Sole is of bad quality, weight of our body"},{"qText":"Which one of these characteristics does a smooth surface has?","options":"Less frictional force, More frictional force, Sometimes less and sometimes more force"},{"qText":"Which of the following is not an advantage of friction?","options":" It enables fallen things to be picked up.\n              It enables vehicles to move on ground.\n              It enables drawing to be made on paper.\n              It enables erasor to remove the pencil marks."},{"qText":"Which of the following will produce the maximum friction? Rubbing of sand paper on _____.","options":"another sand paper, aluminium frame, glazed paper, glass table top"}]}]}]}